===Noun===
'''law''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''laws''')

#<!--DefA--> A [[written]] or [[understood]] [[rule]] that [[concern]]s [[behaviour]]s and the [[appropriate]] [[consequence]]s [[thereof]].  Laws are usually associated with [[mores]].
#<!--DefB--> The [[body]] of written rules governing a [[society]].
#<!--DefC--> A [[one-sided]] [[contract]].
#<!--DefD--> An [[observed]] [[physical]] law.
#<!--DefG-->{{mathematics}} A [[statement]] that is true under specified [[condition]]s.
#<!--DefE--> A [[category]] of [[English]] "[[common law]]" [[petition]]s that [[request]] [[monetary]] [[relief]], as opposed to relief in forms other than a monetary [[judgment]]; compare to "[[equity]]".
#<!--DefF-->{{cricket}} One of the [[official]] rules of [[cricket]] as [[codified]] by the [[MCC]].
#<!--DefH-->{{slang}} (''uncountable'') The [[police]].
#:''Here comes the law - run!''

